the systematic racism

01:20:28.754 --> 01:20:30.377
that happens in this country.

01:20:30.411 --> 01:20:35.278
We need to dismantle the
institutions that continue

01:20:35.313 --> 01:20:37.936
to keep not just
African-Americans

01:20:37.971 --> 01:20:41.457
but people of color
in general subjugated

01:20:41.491 --> 01:20:46.220
and it's difficult but it's
something that needs to happen.

01:20:47.670 --> 01:20:52.192
HORNE: We need an official
government commission

01:20:52.226 --> 01:20:55.851
to investigate and interrogate

01:20:55.885 --> 01:21:01.580
the lingering impact
of both slavery and Jim Crow.

01:21:02.029 --> 01:21:08.449
Perhaps we need also some
way to repair the damage.

01:21:10.969 --> 01:21:13.385
LITWACK:
I would think that the
reparations that would be

01:21:13.420 --> 01:21:17.596
a practical achievement would
take the form of refurbishing

01:21:17.631 --> 01:21:20.945
the black community
in terms of

01:21:20.979 --> 01:21:23.602
the quality of schools
and quality of housing.

01:21:24.949 --> 01:21:27.192
There's a significant
economic change.

01:21:27.952 --> 01:21:31.334
[♪♪♪]

01:21:36.615 --> 01:21:39.549
CAUSEY:
Leveling the playing field
for African-Americans

01:21:39.584 --> 01:21:42.276
seems to be one big answer.

01:21:42.690 --> 01:21:45.141
We tried this
with reconstruction

01:21:45.176 --> 01:21:47.247
and with the
Civil Rights Movement.

01:21:47.626 --> 01:21:51.458
We saw what happened with
the pioneering black Canadians

01:21:51.492 --> 01:21:54.495
and the freed slaves
of Robert Carter

01:21:54.530 --> 01:21:57.533
who made the most
of their opportunities.

01:21:59.259 --> 01:22:03.919
Today, their descendants continue to pursue their dreams

01:22:03.953 --> 01:22:06.749
in whatever ways they choose.

01:22:09.338 --> 01:22:12.789
